      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RACH (1) had to be used up early from a wide gate at Canberra and didn't finish it off. Placed at Canterbury and here prior and draws inside today with the blinkers on again. Well-placed to win. ZAMAZING (4) raced on the speed last start and battled on well but found one better over 1350m at Wyong. Has a low barrier, a handy 2kg claim and is going well enough to take this out. RUBILACE (2) went close here 8-days ago over this distance spiking her figures. She can make the finish building on that. QUADRIA (8) wasn't fancied at Newcastle but was only beaten 1.8L at Hawkesbury prior. Presents fitter and can go a lot better.",
